  "text": "The Envoy TLS certificate validation pipeline is implemented across multiple C++ source files in the envoyproxy/envoy repository (v1.31.2). Here's a comprehensive breakdown of the key components:\n\n## 1. Abstract CertValidator Interface\n**File**: `source/common/tls/cert_validator/cert_validator.h`\n\nDefines the `CertValidator` abstract class with pure virtual methods:\n- `addClientValidationContext()`: Configures client certificate validation for an SSL context\n- `doVerifyCertChain()`: Performs the main certificate chain verification (can be asynchronous)\n- `initializeSslContexts()`: Initializes SSL contexts with validation configuration\n- `updateDigestForSessionId()`: Updates hash for session ID calculation based on validation config\n- Helper methods for retrieving CA certificate info and expiration times\n\nThe `ValidationResults` struct carries status (Pending, Successful, Failed), detailed status, TLS alerts, and error details.\n\n## 2. DefaultCertValidator (X.509 Chain Verification)\n**Files**: `source/common/tls/cert_validator/default_validator.h`, `.cc`\n\nThe `DefaultCertValidator` class implements the CertValidator interface for standard X.509 certificate validation:\n- **Chain Verification**: Uses OpenSSL/BoringSSL X509_STORE_CTX for X.509 chain validation\n- **Certificate Pinning**: `verifyCertificateHashList()` for SHA-256 hash-based pinning\n- **SPKI Pinning**: `verifyCertificateSpkiList()` for Subject Public Key Information pinning\n- **SAN Verification**: `verifySubjectAltName()` for string-based SAN matching and `matchSubjectAltName()` for pattern-based matching\n- **CRL Support**: Handles certificate revocation lists loaded from CA certificates\n- **Configuration**: Supports trust verification, untrusted certificate acceptance, and certificate hash lists\n\nThe factory class `DefaultCertValidatorFactory` creates instances of DefaultCertValidator.\n\n## 3. SAN Matcher (Subject Alternative Name Matching)\n**Files**: `source/common/tls/cert_validator/san_matcher.h`, `.cc`\n\nImplements flexible Subject Alternative Name matching:\n- **SanMatcher Interface**: Pure virtual `match()` method for checking if a GENERAL_NAME matches criteria\n- **StringSanMatcher Class**: Concrete implementation supporting multiple SAN types:\n  - `GEN_DNS`: Domain name matching with wildcard support and regex patterns\n  - `GEN_URI`: URI matching\n  - `GEN_EMAIL`: Email address matching\n  - `GEN_IPADD`: IP address matching\n  - `GEN_OTHERNAME`: OID-based \"Other Name\" matching with custom ASN.1 objects\n- **createStringSanMatcher()**: Factory function that creates appropriate matchers based on `SubjectAltNameMatcher` protobuf configuration\n- Uses `StringMatcherImpl` for flexible pattern matching (exact, prefix, suffix, regex, contains)\n\n## 4. ContextImpl (TLS Context Management)\n**Files**: \n- `source/common/tls/context_impl.h`, `.cc`: Base implementation\n- `source/common/tls/client_context_impl.h`, `.cc`: Client-side specialization\n- `source/common/tls/server_context_impl.h`, `.cc`: Server-side specialization\n\nThe `ContextImpl` class manages:\n- **TLS Contexts**: Maintains `std::vector<Ssl::TlsContext> tls_contexts_` where each contains:\n  - `ssl_ctx_`: BoringSSL SSL_CTX\n  - `cert_chain_`: X509 certificate chain\n  - `ocsp_response_`: Unique OCSP response wrapper\n  - `is_ecdsa_`, `is_must_staple_`: Certificate properties\n- **Certificate Validator**: Holds `CertValidatorPtr cert_validator_` for performing validations\n- **Custom Verify Callback**: Static `customVerifyCallback()` for asynchronous certificate validation\n- **OCSP Support**: `secondsUntilFirstOcspResponseExpires()` queries OCSP response expiration\n- **Asynchronous Validation**: `customVerifyCertChain()` and `customVerifyCertChainForQuic()` for async cert validation\n\nServerContextImpl additionally handles:\n- OCSP stapling with policies (Lenient, Strict, Must Staple)\n- `ocspStapleAction()`: Determines whether to staple OCSP response based on client capabilities\n- Server Name Indication (SNI) based certificate selection\n- TLS context selection via `selectTlsContext()` and `findTlsContext()` methods\n\n## 5. OCSP Response Parsing and Stapling\n**Files**: `source/common/tls/ocsp/ocsp.h`, `.cc`, `asn1_utility.h`, `.cc`\n\nComprehensive OCSP (Online Certificate Status Protocol) support:\n- **OcspResponse Structure**: Top-level DER-encoded OCSP response containing status and response data\n- **OcspResponseStatus Enum**: Reflects RFC 6960 status codes (Successful, MalformedRequest, InternalError, TryLater, SigRequired, Unauthorized)\n- **BasicOcspResponse**: Implements the standard OCSP response format with single certificate status per response\n- **OcspResponseWrapperImpl**: Wraps DER-encoded OCSP responses and provides:\n  - `matchesCertificate()`: Verifies response is for a specific certificate\n  - `isExpired()`: Checks if response's nextUpdate has passed\n  - `secondsUntilExpiration()`: Calculates time until expiration\n  - `getThisUpdate()`, `getNextUpdate()`: Validity window accessors\n- **Asn1OcspUtility**: ASN.1 parsing utilities for OCSP structures:\n  - `parseOcspResponse()`: Parses DER-encoded OCSP response\n  - `parseResponseStatus()`: Extracts OCSP response status\n  - `parseResponseBytes()`: Parses response data\n  - `parseBasicOcspResponse()`: Parses BasicOcspResponse structure\n\nOCSP responses are stored in `TlsContext::ocsp_response_` and ServerContextImpl manages stapling policies in `server_context_impl.h` using `OcspStaplePolicy` (Lenient, Strict, MustStaple).\n\n## 6. SPIFFE Validator (Alternative Implementation)\n**Files**: `source/extensions/transport_sockets/tls/cert_validator/spiffe/spiffe_validator.h`, `.cc`\n\nAlternative CertValidator implementation for SPIFFE (Secure Production Identity Framework For Everyone):\n- Extends CertValidator interface for trust bundle-based validation\n- `trustBundleStores()`: Maintains per-trust-domain X509_STORE for verification\n- `extractTrustDomain()`: Parses SPIFFE identity from URI SANs\n- `certificatePrecheck()`: Validates certificate structure before chain verification\n- `matchSubjectAltName()`: Uses SAN matchers for SPIFFE-specific validation\n- Supports expired certificate allowance for testing\n\n## Integration Flow\n\nThe complete pipeline works as follows:\n1. **Initialization**: ContextImpl creates a CertValidator (typically DefaultCertValidator) and calls `initializeSslContexts()`\n2. **Handshake**: During TLS handshake, OpenSSL invokes the custom verify callback registered with `SSL_CTX_set_custom_verify()`\n3. **Validation**: ContextImpl's `customVerifyCallback()` delegates to `doVerifyCertChain()` on the CertValidator\n4. **Chain Verification**: DefaultCertValidator performs X.509 chain validation using X509_STORE_CTX\n5. **SAN Matching**: After chain verification, StringSanMatchers validate the certificate's Subject Alternative Names\n6. **Async Handling**: For async validators, ValidateResultCallback is invoked when validation completes\n7. **OCSP Support**: ServerContextImpl manages OCSP responses, checking expiration via OcspResponseWrapperImpl\n8. **Result**: ValidationResults with status and error details are returned to the SSL library\n\nThis architecture provides a flexible, pluggable certificate validation system supporting standard X.509 validation, SPIFFE identity verification, OCSP stapling, and custom validation logic."
}

